		<title>Comment on Steeling your knife &#8211; explained by info@razor-edge-knives.com</title>
		<link>http://www.razoredgeknives.com/?p=137#comment-69</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[info@razor-edge-knives.com]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 22 Sep 2015 05:44:31 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.razoredgeknives.com/?p=137#comment-69</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[I like ceramic vs. the smooth steel because it actually removes a little amount of metal each time you use it, creating a fresh apex instead of just bending it back and forth like a smooth steel does. The key is to use it alternating strokes w/ very light pressure until your edge is sharp again. Thanks!]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I like ceramic vs. the smooth steel because it actually removes a little amount of metal each time you use it, creating a fresh apex instead of just bending it back and forth like a smooth steel does. The key is to use it alternating strokes w/ very light pressure until your edge is sharp again. Thanks!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
